==English==

===Etymology===
From {{suffix|en|Texas|an}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈtɛksən/}}
* {{rhymes|en|ɛksən}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Of or pertaining to the inhabitants of the U.S. state of [[Texas]].
# (less common) Of or pertaining to the U.S. state of [[Texas]] in general.

====Usage notes====
Unlike many [[demonym]]s, the adjective normally used to refer to the state is ''Texas'', not ''Texan'' (e.g. the ''Texas capital'', not the ''Texan capital''). ''Texan'' is normally used only in contexts referring to the people.

